The paper deals with the optimization of policies in Decentralized MDPs, which is a problem commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of structured agent interactions is a key aspect of the proposed model, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also proposes a mathematical program formulation, which falls under the sub-category of discrete optimization (cs.DC). Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of policies in complex systems, which may be relevant to the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY).
